<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-12-11T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-12-11T11:00:00-05:00" n="239" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d239">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/1994</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Norway</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SAG1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Schmedeman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Christiania</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-12-11T17:00:00+01:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">December 11, 1915, 5 p. m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 5.30 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>44. Norwegian buyers of American copper and copper wire have been
                                informed by Norwegian American line that British Government has
                                instructed the line to discontinue carrying said goods to Norway
                                where large amounts are used and whose other sources of supply are
                                cut off. British Government demands shipment on British vessels via
                                Great Britain in which event Norwegian buyers fear that goods will
                                not reach them.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_SAG1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schmedeman</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>